# AWS ELB + AUTO SCALING (EASY STEP-BY-STEP)

## AIM
Distribute traffic using Load Balancer and automatically scale EC2 instances.

---

# PART 1: CREATE EC2 INSTANCES

## STEP 1: LAUNCH EC2 INSTANCE 1
1. Go to EC2 → Launch Instance  
2. Name: webserver-1  
3. AMI: Amazon Linux 2  
4. Instance type: t2.micro  
5. Security Group:
   - SSH (22) → My IP  
   - HTTP (80) → Anywhere  
6. Click Launch  

---

## STEP 2: SETUP WEB SERVER (INSTANCE 1)

Connect via SSH and run:
yum update -y
yum install httpd -y
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "This is Server 1" > /var/www/html/index.html


---

## STEP 3: LAUNCH EC2 INSTANCE 2
Repeat same steps as above:

- Name: webserver-2  

---

## STEP 4: SETUP WEB SERVER (INSTANCE 2)
yum update -y
yum install httpd -y
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
echo "This is Server 2" > /var/www/html/index.html


---

# PART 2: CREATE LOAD BALANCER (ALB)

## STEP 5: CREATE SECURITY GROUP
1. Go to EC2 → Security Groups → Create  
2. Name: lb-sg  
3. Allow:
   - HTTP (80) → Anywhere  
4. Save  

---

## STEP 6: CREATE APPLICATION LOAD BALANCER
1. Go to EC2 → Load Balancers  
2. Click Create → Application Load Balancer  

Configure:
- Name: my-alb  
- Scheme: Internet-facing  
- IP: IPv4  

---

## STEP 7: CONFIGURE NETWORK
1. Select default VPC  
2. Select all subnets  

---

## STEP 8: ATTACH SECURITY GROUP
- Select lb-sg  

---

## STEP 9: CREATE TARGET GROUP
1. Name: web-servers-tg  
2. Target type: Instance  
3. Protocol: HTTP  
4. Port: 80  
5. Health check path: /  

---

## STEP 10: REGISTER INSTANCES
1. Select:
   - webserver-1  
   - webserver-2  
2. Click Register  

---

## STEP 11: CREATE LOAD BALANCER
1. Review settings  
2. Click Create  

---

## STEP 12: TEST LOAD BALANCER
1. Copy DNS name of ALB  
2. Open in browser  

Refresh multiple times →  
You will see:
- This is Server 1  
- This is Server 2  

---

# PART 3: AUTO SCALING

## STEP 13: CREATE AMI
1. Go to EC2 → Instances  
2. Select one instance  
3. Actions → Image → Create Image  
4. Name: my-webserver-AMI  
5. Click Create  

---

## STEP 14: CREATE LAUNCH TEMPLATE
1. Go to Launch Templates → Create  
2. Name: my-launch-template  
3. AMI: my-webserver-AMI  
4. Instance type: t2.micro  
5. Security group: allow HTTP  
6. Click Create  

---

## STEP 15: CREATE AUTO SCALING GROUP
1. Go to Auto Scaling Groups → Create  
2. Name: webserver-asg  
3. Launch template: my-launch-template  
4. Click Next  

---

## STEP 16: NETWORK SETTINGS
1. Select VPC  
2. Select all subnets  
3. Attach existing Load Balancer  
4. Select my-alb  

---

## STEP 17: SET CAPACITY
- Desired: 2  
- Min: 1  
- Max: 4  

Click Next → Create  

---

## STEP 18: VERIFY AUTO SCALING
1. Go to Target Groups  
2. Check instances → Healthy  

---

## STEP 19: TEST AUTO SCALING
1. Terminate one EC2 instance  
2. Wait few minutes  

✅ New instance will be created automatically  

---

## STEP 20: FINAL TEST
1. Open Load Balancer DNS  
2. Refresh multiple times  

✅ Traffic is balanced across instances  

---

# FINAL RESULT
- Load Balancer distributes traffic  
- Auto Scaling maintains instance count  
- Fault tolerance achieved  

---

